The brain disease, Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy or "mad cow
disease" ravaged British herds, killing 122,000 cows between 1986 and
1994. It was an economic burden, threatened the beef industry and
alarmed the populace. Researchers were studying its possible link to a
human disease, Creutzfeldt-Jakob, which exhibits similar
symptoms.</SUM>
